        <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Discussion">
          <title>Discussion</title>
          <p>The recent discovery of <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Typhloglomeris</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">caucasica</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> in a pitfall trap in forest near Sochi indicates that the ecological status of this species is a troglophile, not a troglobite, when it occurs in caves in the same area. This record emphasizes the need to carefully collect near and outside caves when assessing the degree of cavernicoly of endogean animals.</p>
